<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="O" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Overween" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Overween</orth> (cf. <emph>O'erween</emph>) to think arrogantly: <cit><quote>you o. to take it so,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.149" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 149</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou dost o. in all,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 1, 29</bibl></cit>. <emph>--ing</emph> == arrogant, presumptuous: <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. III, 1, 157</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 5, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.147" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 147</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.159" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 159</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.328" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 328</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>